column3: Influenza is a viral infection that attacks your respiratory system - your nose throat and lungs. Influenza is commonly called the flu but it's not the same as stomach "flu" viruses that cause diarrhea and vomiting.
Coronaviruses are a type of virus. There are many different kinds and some cause disease. A coronavirus identified in 2019 SARS-CoV-2 has caused a pandemic of respiratory illness called COVID-19.
